Experiment — Disk Scheduling using FCFS

Aim
To implement FCFS Disk Scheduling Algorithm.

Algorithm
Read disk request sequence.
Read initial head position.
Move disk head in request order.
Calculate seek time:
Distance = |Current Head - Request|
Add total seek time.
Display seek sequence and total seek time.



Program
#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

int main()
{
    int n, i;
    int req[50];
    int head, total = 0;

    printf("Enter number of disk requests: ");
    scanf("%d", &n);

    printf("Enter disk request sequence:\n");

    for(i = 0; i < n; i++)
    {
        scanf("%d", &req[i]);
    }

    printf("Enter initial head position: ");
    scanf("%d", &head);

    printf("\nSeek Sequence:\n");

    for(i = 0; i < n; i++)
    {
        printf("%d -> ", req[i]);

        total += abs(req[i] - head);

        head = req[i];
    }

    printf("\n\nTotal Seek Time = %d\n", total);

    return 0;
}


Compile and Run
gcc diskfcfs.c
./a.out


